  "body": "Currently, (best-effort) watch bookmarks are sent just right before the given watch is supposed to timeout:\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/3b00d7dce51b3833815e2459e3a92ed917402170/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher/cacher.go#L1243\r\n\r\nIn https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/90091 we're adjusting how the size of watch cache is determined and make it dynamic and more duration-oriented (rather than based on some magic constants) - we're targeting to always keep 5 minutes of history in watch cache.\r\n\r\nWith that change, we should get back to our bookmark policy:\r\n- change it to (additionally to right before timeout) also send bookmarks every N seconds (setting N to slightly less than expected watch cache history period, so slightly less than X minutes we will use there)\r\n- scale-test this change (to see if it doesn't introduce non-negligible overhead)\r\n- if so permanently introduce this change\r\n\r\n/sig scalability api-machinery",
